<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1869-09-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1869-09-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="432" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d432">
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Milledge</persName>,
                                    district attorney, to Mr. <persName type="to">Hoar</persName>,
                                    Attorney-General.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <dateline><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Atlanta,
                                    Georgia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1869-09-02"><hi rend="italic">September</hi> 2,
                                    1869</date>.</dateline>
                            <p rend="flushleft">To Attorney-General <hi rend="smallcaps">E. R.
                                    Hoar</hi>:</p>
                            <p><seg type="margin">[110]</seg> Large parties are organizing in this
                                State for Cuba. Twenty-five have been arrested in Macon. I leave for
                                that place to night. Can the military be used *to assist in
                                arresting? Please answer to Macon.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>JOHN MILLEDGE,<lb/><hi rend="italic">District
                                    Attorney.</hi></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>